-- Germany Pledges $3.8 Million for Philippine Climate Protection
-- B y   S t e f a n   N i c o l a
-- 2012-09-11T07:50:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-11/germany-pledges-3-8-million-for-philippine-climate-protection.html
Germany pledged 3 million euros
($3.8 million) to help the Philippines cope with the effects of
 climate change .  The money will support climate policies and raise the share
of renewable-energy generators, the German Environment Ministry
said today in an e-mailed statement. Germany has offered more
than 30 million euros for climate protection in the Philippines
since 2008, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stefan Nicola in Berlin at 
